{"type":"message","id":"a6b02c63","parentId":"8a925a84","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:41:27.389Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` is triggered when there are planned orders but no journal records. The issue is that the aggressive strategy has 0 journal records while having 12 planned orders, while defensive and balanced both have 1 journal record each.\n\nThe key question is: why does aggressive have 0 journal records while defensive and balanced each have 1? This seems to be a data issue - the aggressive probe guard didn't have any journal entries recorded for 20260327.\n\nBut wait, the question is about why aggressive's risk control is \"more strict\" than the other two. Looking at the issue:\n- Aggressive: `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` (RED, limit=0) - this is a hard stop because the limit is 0\n\n\n- Defensive: `SHARPE_20D_BREACH` (YELLOW, limit=0.1)\n- Balanced: no issues\n\nThe rule itself applies equally to all three, but aggressive is hitting it hardest because it has zero journal records while the others each have one. This could stem from how the orders were generated or executed differently across strategies, or possibly a data capture issue specific to the aggressive run.\n\nLooking at the config, the aggressive settings do have looser stop-loss thresholds and higher position limits, which might explain why it's behaving differently - but that actually makes it less strict, not more. I need to examine the probe guard script more closely to see where the string matching for \"planned_orders\" is happening and why aggressive is triggering this particular rule.","thinkingSignature":"319546c23f4b2aabb3e75c2cbe7464945e03519f789630494c06d11eafa2999a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xriaqr6jk88h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"planned_orders\\|journal\\|threshold\\|cap\\|limit\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py | head -60"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xriaqr6jk88h_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system -name \"*.yaml\" -o -name \"*.yml\" | xargs grep -l \"probe_guard\\|guard\" 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10079,"output":468,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35567,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842074888,"responseId":"061923dbf79a91d8de4561236b9ecaa6"}}
