{"type":"message","id":"70477324","parentId":"3cb5ae31","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:41:42.006Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the key logic at lines 156-161:\n\n```python\njournal_records = int(len(journal_df))\nif journal_records <= int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\"), 0.0)) and positions_df.empty:\n    if len(orders_df) > 0:\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS\", \"value\": int(len(orders_df)), \"limit\": 0})\n    else:\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"NO_ACTIVITY_DAY\", ...})\n\n\n```\n\nThe rule triggers RED when there are planned orders but no journal records, and this check applies uniformly across all strategies. Defensive and balanced each have 1 journal record, so they don't hit this condition, while aggressive has 0 records with 12 planned orders, triggering the RED alert.\n\nThe real question is why aggressive had no journal entries on 20260327 despite having planned orders—it could be that the orders were proposed but never executed, the journal entry failed to record, or there's a path/permission issue specific to that run. The \"strictness\" here really stems from having 0 journal records while other strategies had at least 1, which suggests something went wrong in aggressive's execution pipeline that day.\n\n```\n- 找到 aggressive 在 20260327 的 journal 文件，检查是否存在\n- 检查其他两个策略的 journal 记录数量对比\n- 查看该日的订单执行报告，看是否有执行差异\n```","thinkingSignature":"c283e26d398728f3aa69a1a374c12085b613da9f44b4940105344a5f5fdfa616"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fo68v8wr1vb1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_aggressive_trading_journal_20260327.csv 2>/dev/null && wc -l /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_aggressive_trading_journal_202