{"type":"message","id":"2189fd3e","parentId":"73ce5fff","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:42:53.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the root cause very clearly. All 12 proposed BUY orders for aggressive on 20260327 were **BLOCKED** with the reason:\n\n```\nstrategy_max_drawdown_pct(24.5200) >= 10.0000\n```\n\nThe aggressive strategy's max drawdown is **24.52%**, which is ABOVE its 10% threshold. This is causing ALL orders to be blocked.\n\nBut wait - the execution brief said:\n- `available_cash: 996111.32` (almost full cash, which makes sense if no orders were filled)\n- `holdings_count: 0` (no holdings, consistent with no fills)\n\n\n- Yet the strategy's live drawdown is reported as 24.52%, exceeding the 10% hard stop, so the risk gate is blocking all new orders\n\nThis is interesting - the probe guard shows a max_drawdown_pct of only 0.39%, which is the paper trading drawdown, but the actual live trading strategy's drawdown is much higher at 24.52%. The risk system appears to be checking the live strategy drawdown rather than the paper trading drawdown when deciding whether to block orders.\n\nSo the chain is: the strategy hits 24.52% drawdown, which exceeds the 10% threshold and blocks all orders, which means nothing gets executed and nothing gets recorded in the journal, triggering the NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS RED alert. Meanwhile, defensive and balanced likely have much lower drawdowns - the defensive probe shows only 0.91% drawdown - so they don't hit these thresholds and can continue trading normally. This reveals a significant flaw in the aggressive strategy's risk management: it's being stopped out not because of current paper trading performance but because of cumulative live trading drawdown. So the pipeline generates orders that get blocked by the strategy-level max drawdown gate, leaving no executed trades to record in the journal—despite having 12 proposed orders that never went through. The guard catches this mismatch as a RED alert, whereas defensive and balanced probably have lower drawdowns that don't trigger the gate, allowing their orders to execute and populate the journal. The solution would involve either adjusting the drawdown threshold for this strategy or reconsidering how live drawdown constraints interact with paper trading records.","thinkingSignature":"58cd727914b763ad4810965370375ff76d1af30018f918849c4415a654c51ab7"},{"type":"text","text":"找到根因了。**aggressive 策略的风控并不是\"更严格\"，而是它的执行链路被一个更深层问题卡住了。**\n\n---\n\n## 核心原因：策略级最大回撤硬拦截\n\n从 `paper_aggressive_orders_v1_20260327.csv` 可以看到，所有 **12 个 BUY 订单全部被 block**：\n\n```\nrisk_gate: blocked\ngate_reason: strategy_max_drawdown_pct(24.5200) >= 10.0000\n```\n\naggressive 策略的**累计实盘最大回撤达到了 24.52%**，超过了 `10%` 的硬止损阈值，导致风控层把所有买单全部拦截。\n\n---\n\n## 为什么其他两个没有这个问题？\n\n| 策略 | 当日状态 | journal 记录 |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| **defensive** | 1 条 journal，0.91% 回撤 | ✅ 正常 |\n| **balanced** | 1 条 journal，1.4% 回撤 | ✅ 正常 |\n| **aggressive** | 0 条 journal，24.52% 策略累计回撤 | ❌ 全部订单被拦截 |\n\ndefensive 的风控配置允许的最大回撤阈值（config 中 `dd_hard`）更高，且实盘累计回撤没超标，所以订单正常执行、写入了 journal。\n\n---\n\n## 告警逻辑\n\n守卫规则的 `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` 是一个**数据一致性检查**——它检测到：\n- `orders_df` 有 12 条计划订单\n- `journal_df` 没有任何执行记录\n\n→ 触发 RED，`halt`。\n\n这个规则本身对三个策略是一样的，但 aggressive 因为\"实盘累计回撤 > 10% 硬止损\"导致**零成交**，才触发了这条告警。\n\n---\n\n## 问题本质\n\naggressive 的 `dd_hard: 0.18`（18%最大回撤）是**策略参数**，但实际触发风控的是 `strategy_max_drawdown_pct >= 10%` 这个**实盘风控硬拦截**——两者不是同一个阈值。实盘累计 24.52% 的回撤已经超过了风控底线，所有订单被静默拦截，没有写入 journal，守卫检测到这个异常，强制 halt。\n\n这不是 aggressive 的风控参数更严格，而是它的实盘累计亏损太大了。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":19940,"output":959,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45919,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774842144371,"responseId":"06192420dc40dd91910b1c45e1615aa9"}}
