{"type":"message","id":"9f86f942","parentId":"ca26905e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:50:02.923Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see! At line 56:\n```python\n\"max_drawdown_pct\": round(max_dd * 100, 2),\n```\n\nThis is computing `max_dd * 100`. `max_dd` is likely from a metrics object. Let me see line 148 where it's used:\n```python\nobjective = metrics[\"annual_return_pct\"] + 6 * metrics[\"sharpe\"] - 0.55 * metrics[\"max_drawdown_pct\"]\n```\n\nSo the `combo_v1.max_drawdown_pct` is computed from a metrics object that has a `max_drawdown_pct` field already in percentage form (not decimal). \n\nNow I need to trace where this metrics object originates and what the `max_dd` variable represents.","thinkingSignature":"642e813461f68a4dd3eb218c943e2a806189991bd5013b68951b52f3d755feba"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ieig3nzh510j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '1,80p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_live_system_v1.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49130,"output":222,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74372,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842597045,"responseId":"061925e50af811497b361faeb5f2a97b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"af91a477","parentId":"9f86f942","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:50:03.084Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ieig3nzh510j_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\n\nimport run_meta_combo_backtest as meta\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nBENCH_CSV = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/index_000852_SH.csv\")\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetaParams:\n    label: str\n    rebalance: str\n    benchmark: str\n    bull_lev: float\n    mid_lev: float\n    bear_lev: float\n    max_gross: float\n    defense_gross_cap: float\n    weekly_stop_trigger: float\n    stop_scale: float\n    cooldown_days: int\n\n\ndef calc_metrics(daily_ret: pd.Series) -> dict:\n    series = daily_ret.dropna().astype(float)\n    if series.empty:\n        return {\n            \"annual_return_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_vol_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"sharpe\": 0.0,\n            \"max_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"final_equity\": 1.0,\n            \"trading_days\": 0,\n        }\n\n    equity = (1 + series).cumprod()\n    annual = float(equity.iloc[-1] ** (252 / len(series)) - 1)\n    annual_vol = float(series.std(ddof=0) * np.sqrt(252))\n    sharpe = annual / annual_vol if annual_vol > 0 else 0.0\n    peak = equity.cummax()\n    max_dd = float(((peak - equity) / peak).max())\n    return {\n        \"annual_return_pct\": round(annual * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_vol_pct\": round(annual_vol * 100, 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(sharpe, 3),\n        \"max_drawdown_pct\": round(max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": round(annual * 100 - max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"final_equity\": round(float(equity.iloc[-1]), 4),\n        \"trading_days\": int(len(series)),\n    }\n\n\ndef benchmark_regime(index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    bench = pd.read_csv(BENCH_CSV)\n    date_col = \"trade_date\" if \"trade_date\" in bench.columns else \"date\"\n    bench[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(bench[date_col].astype(str), errors=\"coerce\")\n    bench = bench.dropna(subset=[\"date\"]).sort_values(\"date\")\n    bench = bench[[\"date\", \"close\"]].dropna()\n    bench = bench.set_index(\"date\").reindex(index).ffill()\n\n    close = bench[\"close\"]\n    ma50 = close.rolling(50).mean()\n    ma120 = close.rolling(120).mean()\n    day_ret = close.pct_change().fillna(0.0)\n\n    regime = pd.Series(\"neutral\", index=index)\n    regime[(close > ma50) & (ma50 > ma120)] = \"bull\"\n    regime[(close < ma120)] = \"bear\"\n    regime[day_ret <= -0.02] = \"crash\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":51,"aggregated":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\n\nimport run_meta_combo_backtest as meta\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nBENCH_CSV = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/index_000852_SH.csv\")\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetaParams:\n    label: str\n    rebalance: str\n    benchmark: str\n    bull_lev: float\n    mid_lev: float\n    bear_lev: float\n    max_gross: float\n    defense_gross_cap: float\n    weekly_stop_trigger: float\n    stop_scale: float\n    cooldown_days: int\n\n\ndef calc_metrics(daily_ret: pd.Series) -> dict:\n    series = daily_ret.dropna().astype(float)\n    if series.empty:\n        return {\n            \"annual_return_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_vol_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"sharpe\": 0.0,\n            \"max_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"final_equity\": 1.0,\n            \"trading_days\": 0,\n        }\n\n    equity = (1 + series).cumprod()\n    annual = float(equity.iloc[-1] ** (252 / len(series)) - 1)\n    annual_vol = float(series.std(ddof=0) * np.sqrt(252))\n    sharpe = annual / annual_vol if annual_vol > 0 else 0.0\n    peak = equity.cummax()\n    max_dd = float(((peak - equity) / peak).max())\n    return {\n        \"annual_return_pct\": round(annual * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_vol_pct\": round(annual_vol * 100, 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(sharpe, 3),\n        \"max_drawdown_pct\": round(max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": round(annual * 100 - max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"final_equity\": round(float(equity.iloc[-1]), 4),\n        \"trading_days\": int(len(series)),\n    }\n\n\ndef benchmark_regime(index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    bench = pd.read_csv(BENCH_CSV)\n    date_col = \"trade_date\" if \"trade_date\" in bench.columns else \"date\"\n    bench[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(bench[date_col].astype(str), errors=\"coerce\")\n    bench = bench.dropna(subset=[\"date\"]).sort_values(\"date\")\n    bench = bench[[\"date\", \"close\"]].dropna()\n    bench = bench.set_index(\"date\").reindex(index).ffill()\n\n    close = bench[\"close\"]\n    ma50 = close.rolling(50).mean()\n    ma120 = close.rolling(120).mean()\n    day_ret = close.pct_change().fillna(0.0)\n\n    regime = pd.Series(\"neutral\", index=index)\n    regime[(close > ma50) & (ma50 > ma120)] = \"bull\"\n    regime[(close < ma120)] = \"bear\"\n    regime[day_ret <= -0.02] = \"crash\"","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774842603063}}
{"type":"message","id":"71399e52","parentId":"af91a477","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:50:08.257Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the `calc_metrics` function computes `max_drawdown_pct` from a daily return series. It uses `max_dd = float(((peak - equity) / peak).max())` which is the standard max drawdown calculation. Then `max_drawdown_pct = round(max_dd * 100, 2)`.\n\nNow I need to find where this is called with the live trading data. The `live_system_v1_20260327.json` has `combo_v1.max_drawdown_pct = 24.52`. This is computed from some backtest result.Let me look at lines 40-60 more carefully and how the combo is built.","thinkingSignature":"cd1218a3f92bae3448f917b50318ebaa6f12dcba45f66dd8bc149f62d339864d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n80emcicffr0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '30,120p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_live_system_v1.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50119,"output":201,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75340,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842603085,"responseId":"061925eb5263307a3b8cd98f871e7573"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a333a04","parentId":"71399e52","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:50:08.381Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n80emcicffr0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"cooldown_days: int\n\n\ndef calc_metrics(daily_ret: pd.Series) -> dict:\n    series = daily_ret.dropna().astype(float)\n    if series.empty:\n        return {\n            \"annual_return_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_vol_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"sharpe\": 0.0,\n            \"max_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"final_equity\": 1.0,\n            \"trading_days\": 0,\n        }\n\n    equity = (1 + series).cumprod()\n    annual = float(equity.iloc[-1] ** (252 / len(series)) - 1)\n    annual_vol = float(series.std(ddof=0) * np.sqrt(252))\n    sharpe = annual / annual_vol if annual_vol > 0 else 0.0\n    peak = equity.cummax()\n    max_dd = float(((peak - equity) / peak).max())\n    return {\n        \"annual_return_pct\": round(annual * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_vol_pct\": round(annual_vol * 100, 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(sharpe, 3),\n        \"max_drawdown_pct\": round(max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": round(annual * 100 - max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"final_equity\": round(float(equity.iloc[-1]), 4),\n        \"trading_days\": int(len(series)),\n    }\n\n\ndef benchmark_regime(index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    bench = pd.read_csv(BENCH_CSV)\n    date_col = \"trade_date\" if \"trade_date\" in bench.columns else \"date\"\n    bench[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(bench[date_col].astype(str), errors=\"coerce\")\n    bench = bench.dropna(subset=[\"date\"]).sort_values(\"date\")\n    bench = bench[[\"date\", \"close\"]].dropna()\n    bench = bench.set_index(\"date\").reindex(index).ffill()\n\n    close = bench[\"close\"]\n    ma50 = close.rolling(50).mean()\n    ma120 = close.rolling(120).mean()\n    day_ret = close.pct_change().fillna(0.0)\n\n    regime = pd.Series(\"neutral\", index=index)\n    regime[(close > ma50) & (ma50 > ma120)] = \"bull\"\n    regime[(close < ma120)] = \"bear\"\n    regime[day_ret <= -0.02] = \"crash\"\n\n    return pd.DataFrame({\"close\": close, \"ma50\": ma50, \"ma120\": ma120, \"regime\": regime, \"bench_ret\": day_ret})\n\n\ndef load_qlib_baseline() -> dict:\n    qlib_json = REPORT_DIR / \"qlib_phase2_baseline_20260306.json\"\n    if qlib_json.exists():\n        return json.loads(qlib_json.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    return {\n        \"note\": \"qlib baseline not found\",\n        \"annualized_return_excess_with_cost_pct\": None,\n        \"max_drawdown_excess_with_cost_pct\": None,\n        \"ic\": None,\n        \"rank_ic\": None,\n    }\n\n\ndef run_meta_line(\n    returns: pd.DataFrame,\n    market_close: pd.Series,\n    params: MetaParams,\n) -> tuple[dict, pd.DataFrame]:\n    summary, curve, _ = meta.run_meta(\n        returns=returns,\n        market_close=market_close,\n        benchmark_code=params.benchmark,\n        k=4,\n        rebalance=params.rebalance,\n        bull_lev=params.bull_lev,\n        mid_lev=params.mid_lev,\n        bear_lev=params.bear_lev,\n        max_gross=params.max_gross,\n        trade_cost=0.0008,\n        score_vol_weight=0.4,\n        score_dd_weight=0.4,\n        defense_gross_cap=params.defense_gross_cap,\n        weekly_stop_trigger=params.weekly_stop_trigger,\n        stop_scale=params.stop_scale,\n        cooldown_days=params.cooldown_days,\n    )\n    curve = curve.copy()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":35,"aggregated":"cooldown_days: int\n\n\ndef calc_metrics(daily_ret: pd.Series) -> dict:\n    series = daily_ret.dropna().astype(float)\n    if series.empty:\n        return {\n            \"annual_return_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_vol_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"sharpe\": 0.0,\n            \"max_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": 0.0,\n            \"final_equity\": 1.0,\n            \"trading_days\": 0,\n        }\n\n    equity = (1 + series).cumprod()\n    annual = float(equity.iloc[-1] ** (252 / len(series)) - 1)\n    annual_vol = float(series.std(ddof=0) * np.sqrt(252))\n    sharpe = annual / annual_vol if annual_vol > 0 else 0.0\n    peak = equity.cummax()\n    max_dd = float(((peak - equity) / peak).max())\n    return {\n        \"annual_return_pct\": round(annual * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_vol_pct\": round(annual_vol * 100, 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(sharpe, 3),\n        \"max_drawdown_pct\": round(max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"annual_minus_drawdown_pct\": round(annual * 100 - max_dd * 100, 2),\n        \"final_equity\": round(float(equity.iloc[-1]), 4),\n        \"trading_days\": int(len(series)),\n    }\n\n\ndef benchmark_regime(index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    bench = pd.read_csv(BENCH_CSV)\n    date_col = \"trade_date\" if \"trade_date\" in bench.columns else \"date\"\n    bench[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(bench[date_col].astype(str), errors=\"coerce\")\n    bench = bench.dropna(subset=[\"date\"]).sort_values(\"date\")\n    bench = bench[[\"date\", \"close\"]].dropna()\n    bench = bench.set_index(\"date\").reindex(index).ffill()\n\n    close = bench[\"close\"]\n    ma50 = close.rolling(50).mean()\n    ma120 = close.rolling(120).mean()\n    day_ret = close.pct_change().fillna(0.0)\n\n    regime = pd.Series(\"neutral\", index=index)\n    regime[(close > ma50) & (ma50 > ma120)] = \"bull\"\n    regime[(close < ma120)] = \"bear\"\n    regime[day_ret <= -0.02] = \"crash\"\n\n    return pd.DataFrame({\"close\": close, \"ma50\": ma50, \"ma120\": ma120, \"regime\": regime, \"bench_ret\": day_ret})\n\n\ndef load_qlib_baseline() -> dict:\n    qlib_json = REPORT_DIR / \"qlib_phase2_baseline_20260306.json\"\n    if qlib_json.exists():\n        return json.loads(qlib_json.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    return {\n        \"note\": \"qlib baseline not found\",\n        \"annualized_return_excess_with_cost_pct\": None,\n        \"max_drawdown_excess_with_cost_pct\": None,\n        \"ic\": None,\n        \"rank_ic\": None,\n    }\n\n\ndef run_meta_line(\n    returns: pd.DataFrame,\n    market_close: pd.Series,\n    params: MetaParams,\n) -> tuple[dict, pd.DataFrame]:\n    summary, curve, _ = meta.run_meta(\n        returns=returns,\n        market_close=market_close,\n        benchmark_code=params.benchmark,\n        k=4,\n        rebalance=params.rebalance,\n        bull_lev=params.bull_lev,\n        mid_lev=params.mid_lev,\n        bear_lev=params.bear_lev,\n        max_gross=params.max_gross,\n        trade_cost=0.0008,\n        score_vol_weight=0.4,\n        score_dd_weight=0.4,\n        defense_gross_cap=params.defense_gross_cap,\n        weekly_stop_trigger=params.weekly_stop_trigger,\n        stop_scale=params.stop_scale,\n        cooldown_days=params.cooldown_days,\n    )\n    curve = curve.copy()","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774842608362}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d92cd54","parentId":"0a333a04","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:50:11.962Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to find where the `combo_v1` is populated with `max_drawdown_pct = 24.52`. Let me look at lines 140-170 and 240-290.","thinkingSignature":"437f3022d9009e95d2134f1767c153e640ea1fd7b6c7e4167ce711db791e7fed"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_83ywduu7h9qk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '130,200p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_live_system_v1.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51263,"output":104,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76387,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842608381,"responseId":"061925f0f28259ede69751dfba734e23"}}
{"type":"message","id":"640391ff","parentId":"5d92cd54","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:50:12.068Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_83ywduu7h9qk_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"best_curve = None\n\n    for bull in [1.0, 1.2, 1.4, 1.6, 1.8, 2.0]:\n        for neutral in [0.8, 1.0, 1.2, 1.4]:\n            for bear in [0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9]:\n                for crash in [0.15, 0.25, 0.35]:\n                    regime_scale = {\n                        \"bull\": bull,\n                        \"neutral\": neutral,\n                        \"bear\": bear,\n                        \"crash\": crash,\n                    }\n\n                    gross = frame[\"regime\"].map(regime_scale).fillna(1.0)\n                    # 小市值线偏进攻，宽基线偏防守\n                    combo_ret = gross * (0.62 * frame[\"weekly\"] + 0.38 * frame[\"monthly\"])\n                    metrics = calc_metrics(combo_ret)\n\n                    objective = metrics[\"annual_return_pct\"] + 6 * metrics[\"sharpe\"] - 0.55 * metrics[\"max_drawdown_pct\"]\n                    candidate = {\n                        \"bull_gross\": bull,\n                        \"neutral_gross\": neutral,\n                        \"bear_gross\": bear,\n                        \"crash_gross\": crash,\n                        \"objective\": round(objective, 3),\n                        **metrics,\n                    }\n\n                    if metrics[\"max_drawdown_pct\"] <= 25.0:\n                        hard_ok = True\n                    else:\n                        hard_ok = False\n\n                    if best is None:\n                        best = (hard_ok, objective, candidate)\n                        best_curve = pd.DataFrame({\"date\": frame.index, \"daily_return\": combo_ret.values})\n                        continue\n\n                    prev_ok, prev_obj, _ = best\n                    if (hard_ok and not prev_ok) or (hard_ok == prev_ok and objective > prev_obj):\n                        best = (hard_ok, objective, candidate)\n                        best_curve = pd.DataFrame({\"date\": frame.index, \"daily_return\": combo_ret.values})\n\n    if best is None or best_curve is None:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"组合优化失败\")\n\n    best_curve[\"equity\"] = (1 + best_curve[\"daily_return\"]).cumprod()\n    peak = best_curve[\"equity\"].cummax()\n    best_curve[\"drawdown\"] = (peak - best_curve[\"equity\"]) / peak\n    return best[2], best_curve\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    REPORT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    stamp = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\n\n    strategy_ids = [\n        \"2024_101\",\n        \"2024_180\",\n        \"2025_038\",\n        \"2020_073\",\n        \"2024_182\",\n        \"2025_024\",\n        \"2023_018\",\n        \"2025_028\",\n    ]\n\n    returns = meta.build_base_returns(strategy_ids=strategy_ids, max_symbols=180)\n    close, _, _, _, _ = meta.batch.load_market_matrices(max_symbols=180)\n    market_close = close.mean(axis=1, skipna=True).reindex(returns.index).ffill()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"best_curve = None\n\n    for bull in [1.0, 1.2, 1.4, 1.6, 1.8, 2.0]:\n        for neutral in [0.8, 1.0, 1.2, 1.4]:\n            for bear in [0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9]:\n                for crash in [0.15, 0.25, 0.35]:\n                    regime_scale = {\n                        \"bull\": bull,\n                        \"neutral\": neutral,\n                        \"bear\": bear,\n                        \"crash\": crash,\n                    }\n\n                    gross = frame[\"regime\"].map(regime_scale).fillna(1.0)\n                    # 小市值线偏进攻，宽基线偏防守\n                    combo_ret = gross * (0.62 * frame[\"weekly\"] + 0.38 * frame[\"monthly\"])\n                    metrics = calc_metrics(combo_ret)\n\n                    objective = metrics[\"annual_return_pct\"] + 6 * metrics[\"sharpe\"] - 0.55 * metrics[\"max_drawdown_pct\"]\n                    candidate = {\n                        \"bull_gross\": bull,\n                        \"neutral_gross\": neutral,\n                        \"bear_gross\": bear,\n                        \"crash_gross\": crash,\n                        \"objective\": round(objective, 3),\n                        **metrics,\n                    }\n\n                    if metrics[\"max_drawdown_pct\"] <= 25.0:\n                        hard_ok = True\n                    else:\n                        hard_ok = False\n\n                    if best is None:\n                        best = (hard_ok, objective, candidate)\n                        best_curve = pd.DataFrame({\"date\": frame.index, \"daily_return\": combo_ret.values})\n                        continue\n\n                    prev_ok, prev_obj, _ = best\n                    if (hard_ok and not prev_ok) or (hard_ok == prev_ok and objective > prev_obj):\n                        best = (hard_ok, objective, candidate)\n                        best_curve = pd.DataFrame({\"date\": frame.index, \"daily_return\": combo_ret.values})\n\n    if best is None or best_curve is None:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"组合优化失败\")\n\n    best_curve[\"equity\"] = (1 + best_curve[\"daily_return\"]).cumprod()\n    peak = best_curve[\"equity\"].cummax()\n    best_curve[\"drawdown\"] = (peak - best_curve[\"equity\"]) / peak\n    return best[2], best_curve\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    REPORT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    stamp = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\n\n    strategy_ids = [\n        \"2024_101\",\n        \"2024_180\",\n        \"2025_038\",\n        \"2020_073\",\n        \"2024_182\",\n        \"2025_024\",\n        \"2023_018\",\n        \"2025_028\",\n    ]\n\n    returns = meta.build_base_returns(strategy_ids=strategy_ids, max_symbols=180)\n    close, _, _, _, _ = meta.batch.load_market_matrices(max_symbols=180)\n    market_close = close.mean(axis=1, skipna=True).reindex(returns.index).ffill()","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774842612048}}
{"type":"message","id":"eab30a78","parentId":"640391ff","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:50:35.359Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. The `combo_v1.max_drawdown_pct = 24.52%` is computed from a **backtest** of a combo strategy that combines weekly and monthly strategy returns. This is NOT the paper trading account's drawdown.\n\nThe `combo_v1` is the result of a grid search over regime parameters (bull/neutral/bear/crash) that optimizes `annual_return + 6 * sharpe - 0.55 * max_drawdown`. The best candidate with `max_drawdown <= 25%` is selected and stored in `combo_v1`.\n\nSo the 24.52% is the historical backtested max drawdown of the COMBO strategy (smallcap weekly + broad monthly), not the paper trading account.\n\n\nNow I see the problem clearly - there's a mismatch between what the paper account actually shows (0.39% drawdown from live trading) and what the gate is checking (24.52% from the backtested combo). The guard is using the strategy's historical backtest performance to restrict the paper trading account, which doesn't reflect what's actually happening in real time.\n\nThe paper account should be managed independently based on its own trading journal, not treated as an extension of the live strategy's risk parameters. The fact that the 24.52% threshold comes from a backtest while the paper account has only experienced a 0.39% drawdown suggests either the paper account was closed before significant losses occurred, or these two systems are being conflated when they shouldn't be. So there are actually two separate drawdown metrics being tracked: the paper account's own 0.39% drawdown from its trading journal, and a 24.52% figure that comes from the live system's backtested combo strategy. The `strategy_max_drawdown_pct` parameter in the gate check is pulling from that live system rather than the paper account itself, which means the guard is comparing against a different benchmark than what the paper account has actually experienced.","thinkingSignature":"b5647662319b23336869596fe510aa615ed3a7d8ec0aba28a5501af018042148"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。\n\n---\n\n## 根因定位\n\n**24.52% 不是纸纸账户的实际回撤，而是来自另一个计算源头。**\n\n完整链路如下：\n\n```\nlive_system_v1_20260327.json\n  └── combo_v1.max_drawdown_pct = 24.52\n          ↑\n          │  来源：run_live_system_v1.py 的组合优化\n          │  过程：对 8 个策略 ID 做双周期（周频+月频）组合，\n          │  按 objective = 年化 + 6×夏普 - 0.55×最大回撤 做网格搜索，\n          │  选出 max_drawdown <= 25% 的最优候选 → 24.52%\n          │\nruntime_risk_state_latest.json（今日 11:35 生成）\n  └── runtime_metrics.strategy_max_dd_pct = 24.52\n          ↓\napply_risk_to_merged_signals.py（订单风控层）\n  └── gate: strategy_max_drawdown_pct(24.52) >= 10.0% → 全部 block\n```\n\n纸纸账户 `paper_aggressive_account_v1` 的实际回撤：\n```\nmax_drawdown_pct = 0.39%   ← 来自 paper journal 的真实交易记录\n```\n\n---\n\n## 问题本质\n\n**两套回撤数据在打架：**\n\n| 数据 | 值 | 来源 |\n|------|-----|------|\n| `combo_v1.max_drawdown_pct` | **24.52%** | 底层驱动策略的历史回测最优结果 |\n| `paper journal drawdown` | **0.39%** | aggressive 纸纸账户的实际交易净值回撤 |\n\n风控层拿的是 **策略组合的历史回测回撤**（24.52%），而不是纸纸账户的实际持仓回撤（0.39%）。策略的历史回测最大回撤确实曾到过 24.52%，触发了 `10%` 的熔断阈值，导致所有买单被静默拒绝。\n\n---\n\n## 需要确认的问题\n\naggressive 的纸纸账户从 20260319 建仓到 20260320 全部清仓，净值从 100 万到 55 万（已纠正回 99.96 万），实际亏损 `-0.39%`。**清仓后一直是空仓**。\n\n但风控层用的是策略的历史回测回撤 24.52% 来判断纸纸账户是否可开仓——这是两个完全不同的数据源。\n\n你觉得应该怎么处置？\n1. 纸纸账户的风控单独用纸纸账户自己的 journal 数据，不再引用 combo_v1 的历史回测回撤\n2. 维持现状（用 combo_v1 的回测数据，但要理解这不是纸纸账户的实际回撤）"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52054,"output":989,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78063,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774842612069,"responseId":"061925f44e623f13df15896c076f07d7"}}
