{"type":"message","id":"7b669ce7","parentId":"2916ad2a","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:53:39.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to fix the second part: in `materialize_profile_signal_chain`, change the `--strategy-max-dd-pct` to use `state.get(\"drawdown_pct\", 0.0)` instead of `runtime_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\")`.\n\nBut wait - I need to be careful. The paper account's `drawdown_pct` might not be the best thing to use here. Let me think again.\n\nActually, looking at the logic:\n- The halt condition in `decide_mode` checks: `strategy_max_drawdown_pct >= target_dd` (where `target_dd = 25.0%`)\n\n\n- But in `apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py`, the `RiskEngine` evaluates the same halt condition\n\nFor paper trading, the correct value to check should be the paper account's **真实持仓回撤**, which is `drawdown_pct` from the paper account JSON. The paper account drawdown of 0.39% is correct and should NOT trigger a halt. So the fix is right - use `state.get(\"drawdown_pct\", 0.0)`.\n\nHowever, there's a subtlety: `drawdown_pct` in the paper account JSON is the running drawdown from the peak of the paper account. This is the correct metric to use for the paper trading halt check. Now I need to modify the command-line argument in `materialize_profile_signal_chain` to use this value instead of the live system's drawdown percentage.","thinkingSignature":"f12f2a9d46cd9eef4b67ac78fc11d17af9ffd6d09b10168395460c394c242ae8"},{"type":"text","text":"**第二处**：`materialize_profile_signal_chain` — 用纸纸账户自己的回撤替换掉 live 策略的回撤\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kzn652djited_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '640,660p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60775,"output":401,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86196,"cost":{"input":0,"