{"type":"message","id":"a66cdef4","parentId":"9205a5c5","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:54:38.275Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct` from the config (line 90, 110) is used in the `RiskEngine` to determine when to enter risk-off mode. But the halt check at line 340 uses `strategy_max_drawdown_pct=runtime_inputs[\"strategy_max_dd_pct\"]`, which is the value passed via `--strategy-max-dd-pct`.My fix changes the value passed via `--strategy-max-dd-pct` from `runtime_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\")` (= 24.52%) to `state.get(\"drawdown_pct\", 0.0)` (= 0.39% for aggressive).\n\n\nSo the halt check will now correctly use the paper account's 0.39% drawdown instead of the live combo's 24.52%. Let me verify this by tracing through the halt condition logic to confirm it won't trigger.","thinkingSignature":"9dfe800464b9f0bfec5f7400986e650add39f0512e631f510ef8d15b056e0afa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vwkbe9ir1oin_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '80,115p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":63976,"output":250,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89246,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842870578,"responseId":"061926f6baa1081da8009a933da53da7"}}
