{"type":"message","id":"9aba0f2b","parentId":"ba63b794","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:54:45.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hk6e9ra40qt3_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"breadth = context.market_breadth\n        breadth_hard_th = self.config.market_breadth_hard_stop_threshold\n        breadth_risk_th = self.config.market_breadth_riskoff_threshold\n        if breadth is not None:\n            if breadth_hard_th is not None and breadth <= breadth_hard_th:\n                hard_stop = True\n                reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"market_breadth\", breadth, breadth_hard_th, \"<=\"))\n            elif breadth_risk_th is not None and breadth <= breadth_risk_th:\n                risk_off = True\n                reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"market_breadth\", breadth, breadth_risk_th, \"<=\"))\n\n        max_dd = context.strategy_max_drawdown_pct\n        max_dd_th = self.config.strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\n        if max_dd_th is not None and max_dd is not None and max_dd >= max_dd_th:\n            risk_off = True\n            reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct\", max_dd, max_dd_th, \">=\"))\n\n        sharpe = context.strategy_sharpe\n        sharpe_th = self.config.strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold\n        if sharpe_th is not None and sharpe is not None and sharpe < sharpe_th:\n            soft_cautious = True\n            reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"strategy_sharpe\", sharpe, sharpe_th, \"<\"))\n\n        if hard_stop:\n            risk_off = True\n            mode = \"halt\"\n            halt_new_buy = True\n        elif risk_off:\n            mode = \"cautious\"\n            halt_new_buy = not self.config.allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\n        elif soft_cautious:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":32,"aggregated":"breadth = context.market_breadth\n        breadth_hard_th = self.config.market_breadth_hard_stop_threshold\n        breadth_risk_th = self.config.market_breadth_riskoff_threshold\n        if breadth is not None:\n            if breadth_hard_th is not None and breadth <= breadth_hard_th:\n                hard_stop = True\n                reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"market_breadth\", breadth, breadth_hard_th, \"<=\"))\n            elif breadth_risk_th is not None and breadth <= breadth_risk_th:\n                risk_off = True\n                reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"market_breadth\", breadth, breadth_risk_th, \"<=\"))\n\n        max_dd = context.strategy_max_drawdown_pct\n        max_dd_th = self.config.strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\n        if max_dd_th is not None and max_dd is not None and max_dd >= max_dd_th:\n            risk_off = True\n            reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct\", max_dd, max_dd_th, \">=\"))\n\n        sharpe = context.strategy_sharpe\n        sharpe_th = self.config.strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold\n        if sharpe_th is not None and sharpe is not None and sharpe < sharpe_th:\n            soft_cautious = True\n            reasons.append(self._fmt_threshold_trigger(\"strategy_sharpe\", sharpe, sharpe_th, \"<\"))\n\n        if hard_stop:\n            risk_off = True\n            mode = \"halt\"\n            halt_new_buy = True\n        elif risk_off:\n            mode = \"cautious\"\n            halt_new_buy = not self.config.allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\n        elif soft_cautious:","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774842885970}}
{"type":"message","id":"aae64c1f","parentId":"9aba0f2b","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:54:57.398Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The RiskEngine in `risk_engine.py` evaluates:\n1. `strategy_max_drawdown_pct` (from context) vs `strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct` (from config, 10% for aggressive)\n2. If `max_dd >= max_dd_th` → `risk_off = True`\n\nBut wait - the `halt` mode is triggered by `hard_stop = True`, which comes from:\n1. `breadth <= breadth_hard_th`\n2. Or other hard stop conditions\n\nAnd the `strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct` only triggers `risk_off = True`, NOT `hard_stop = True`.\n\n\nSo the issue at line 167 is that when the strategy's drawdown exceeds the 10% threshold, it only sets `risk_off = True`, which means `halt_new_buy` depends on `allow_new_buy_when_riskoff`. Let me check the aggressive config to see what that setting actually is. So the halt condition is actually triggered somewhere else, not in the risk engine itself. Looking back at the order file, the gate reason shows the strategy's max drawdown at 24.52% exceeds the 10% threshold, which is what's causing the halt. This means there's likely a hard-stop check happening in the code that calls the risk engine, separate from the risk-off logic I was examining.\n\nThe risk engine only sets `risk_off = True` when drawdown exceeds the threshold, but `halt_new_buy` only becomes true if `hard_stop = True`, which would need to come from a different condition like breadth or some other hard-stop trigger. Yet the aggressive config shows `allow_new_buy_when_riskoff: true`, which means even with `risk_off` triggered, new buys should still be allowed.\n\nI'm getting confused about where the halt is actually being enforced. Let me trace through the prewrite guard script to see how `halt_new_buy` is being set in the paper trading pipeline, since that's likely where the actual blocking is happening.","thinkingSignature":"7b3f1986f84840f99c9be29719ffe341ab93fae1529e6e00c8107d94ce1b280b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6bj8w4xsnq8c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"halt_new_buy\\|hard_stop\\|halt\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65658,"output":499,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91177,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842885987,"responseId":"06192706c22a888594c74e5cbfc942ee"}}
