{"type":"message","id":"60b58fa9","parentId":"2dac9577","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:55:05.408Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `hard_stop=args.hard_stop` is passed directly from command line args. Let me check if there's a `--hard-stop` argument being passed from `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py`.Actually, looking at the command built in `materialize_profile_signal_chain`:```python\napply_cmd = [\n    \"python3\",\n    \"scripts/apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py\",\n    \"--input\",\n    ...\n    \"--strategy-max-dd-pct\",\n    str(state.get(\"drawdown_pct\", 0.0)),  # MY FIX\n    ...\n]\n```\n\nThere's NO `--hard-stop` argument passed! So `hard_stop` defaults to `False` in the argparse.So in `apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py`, the halt check for `strategy_max_drawdown_pct` only triggers `risk_off = True`, NOT `hard_stop`. \n\nBut here's the thing - the blocking logic I'm seeing doesn't come from `apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py`. The gate reason mentioning `strategy_max_drawdown_pct(24.5200) >= 10.0000` is actually coming from `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` directly. Let me trace where this gate reason is actually being set.","thinkingSignature":"ed45cd8881856cfc17f4f2e88ed1922cf0d89801f7b9b849bbab54a16a999a72"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4bnn638rbyhs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"strategy_max_drawdown_pct\\|strategy_max_dd\\|hard_stop\\|gate_reason\\|blocked\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":66448,"output":338,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91806,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842897523,"responseId":"06192711e5802ef367c003914507eb8f"}}
