{"type":"message","id":"61760ffc","parentId":"5692dca6","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:55:42.984Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture:\n\n1. In `run_live_execution_v1.py`, the `size_orders` function checks `runtime.halt_new_buy` (line 2057)\n2. If `runtime.halt_new_buy == True`, then `blocked_buy_halt += 1` and `risk_gate = \"blocked\"` with `gate_reason = runtime.halt_reason`\n\nThe `runtime.halt_reason` is `\"组合历史回撤24.52% >= 目标上限10.0%\"`.\n\nThe `runtime` object comes from `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py`'s call to `resolve_runtime_state`. Let me look at how `runtime` is built in `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py`.\n\n\nLooking at line 211 in `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py`, the code is setting `hard_stop` and `gate_reasons` from an `authoritative` object that gets resolved through `resolve_authoritative_runtime`. The `halt_reason` that ends up in the order gate is being pulled from this authoritative runtime state, which is where the drawdown threshold check is happening. So `runtime.halt_new_buy` is actually set based on `runtime_metrics.get(\"halt_new_buy\")`, not `runtime.hard_stop`. I need to look more carefully at line 211 to see what's actually being assigned to `runtime.halt_new_buy`.","thinkingSignature":"316053c36958bc0ed1af074a2e20f56812576cd5f44c200641b47ac86f64491e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gsjpy0pmxoa2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '200,230p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69808,"output":351,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95179,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774842933962,"responseId":"0619273644569224099e38786d360e3d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d8860c3","parentId":"61760ffc","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:55:43.109Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gsjpy0pmxoa2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"runtime_latest = runtime_metrics.get(\"runtime_latest\") or {}\n    source = runtime_metrics.get(\"source\")\n    if source != \"runtime_risk_state_latest\":\n        return runtime\n\n    authoritative = runtime_truth if isinstance(runtime_truth, dict) and runtime_truth else runtime_latest\n    if not isinstance(authoritative, dict) or not authoritative:\n        return runtime\n\n    runtime.mode = str(authoritative.get(\"mode\") or getattr(runtime, \"mode\", \"\") or \"\")\n    runtime.risk_off = bool(authoritative.get(\"risk_off\", getattr(runtime, \"risk_off\", False)))\n    runtime.hard_stop = bool(authoritative.get(\"hard_stop\", getattr(runtime, \"hard_stop\", False)))\n    runtime.halt_new_buy = bool(authoritative.get(\"halt_new_buy\", getattr(runtime, \"halt_new_buy\", False)))\n    runtime.halt_reason = str(\n        authoritative.get(\"trading_status_reason\")\n        or authoritative.get(\"state_reason\")\n        or authoritative.get(\"halt_reason\")\n        or getattr(runtime, \"halt_reason\", \"\")\n        or \"\"\n    )\n    gate_reasons = authoritative.get(\"gate_reasons\")\n    if isinstance(gate_reasons, list):\n        runtime.gate_reasons = [str(item).strip() for item in gate_reasons if str(item).strip()]\n    market_breadth = authoritative.get(\"market_breadth\", runtime_metrics.get(\"market_breadth\"))\n    if market_breadth is not None:\n        try:\n            runtime.market_breadth = float(market_breadth)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    return runtime"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":33,"aggregated":"runtime_latest = runtime_metrics.get(\"runtime_latest\") or {}\n    source = runtime_metrics.get(\"source\")\n    if source != \"runtime_risk_state_latest\":\n        return 