{"type":"message","id":"17742099","parentId":"bea8e009","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:54:05.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `OPENCLAW_BIN` is pointing to `~/.local/share/fnm/aliases/default/bin/openclaw`. But the error says `env: node: No such file or directory`. This means the `openclaw` binary itself starts with `#!/usr/bin/env node` or similar shebang, and the env can't find node in cron's minimal PATH.\n\nThe fix is to set `PATH` in the subprocess call to include the fnm path. Let me modify the `send_feishu` function to include the full PATH.\n\nAlso, the `mcporter` issue - it's called without a full path. Let me fix both.","thinkingSignature":"8ca580b7061d750f7054ad7eaf3abb529aecc8bf89ef0ea24180366c05897cc5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qqazf9fiz3wx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -5 /Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/aliases/default/bin/openclaw"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37983,"output":174,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63177,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774875239471,"responseId":"0619a5670d5880322b63303d30cd4482"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d046ba8","parentId":"17742099","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:54:05.568Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qqazf9fiz3wx_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\nimport { readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { access } from \"node:fs/promises\";\nimport module from \"node:module\";"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":31,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\nimport { readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { access } from \"node:fs/promises\";\nimport module from \"node:module\";","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774875245554}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9d86ac8","parentId":"7d046ba8","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:54:19.945Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The openclaw binary starts with `#!/usr/bin/env node` - it needs node in the PATH when executed. In cron, the PATH is minimal, so it can't find node.\n\nThe fix is to add the full node path to the environment when running the subprocess. Let me modify `cron_weibo_monitor.py` to set the PATH in the subprocess call.\n\nFor `mcporter` in `fetch_and_report.py`, I also need to use the full path.\n\nLet me also check if there's a way to set the PATH more globally in the cron job, but the cleanest fix is to patch the scripts.","thinkingSignature":"21b643a566e6026f79bdb5db12b0f58a42d883c58f263d8da7ffbb1def63930d"},{"type":"text","text":"`openclaw` 的 shebang 是 `#!/usr/bin/env node`，cron 里找不到 node。修复两处：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gtan6vc170v6_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"old_text":"def send_feishu(message: str, dry_run: bool = False) -> tuple:\n    cmd = [\n        OPENCLAW_BIN,\n        \"message\", \"send\",\n        \"--channel\", \"feishu\",\n        \"--target\", FEISHU_TARGET,\n        \"-m\", message,\n    ]\n    if dry_run:\n        cmd.append(\"--dry-run\")\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=60)\n        return result.returncode == 0, result.stdout[:500] or result.stderr[:500]\n    except Exception as e:\n        return False, str(e)","newText":"def send_feishu(message: str, dry_run: bool = False) -> tuple:\n    # cron 环境 PATH 不含 fnm node 路径，需要显式传入\n    fnm_bin = str(Path.home() / \".local\" / \"share\" / \"fnm\" / \"node-versions\" / \"v22.22.0\" / \"installation\" / \"bin\")\n    env = {**os.environ, \"PATH\": f\"{fnm_bin}:{os.environ.get('PATH', '')}\"}\n    cmd = [\n        OPENCLAW_BIN,\n        \"message\", \"send\",\n        \"--channel\", \"feishu\",\n        \"--target\", FEISHU_TARGET,\n        \"-m\", message,\n    ]\n    if dry_run:\n        cmd.append(\"--dry-run\")\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=60, env=env)\n        return result.returncode == 0, result.stdout[:500] or result.stderr[:500]\n    except Exception as e:\n        return False, str(e)","file":"/Users/ling/workspace/weibo-monitor/cron_weibo_monitor.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38212,"output":558,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63790,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774875245568,"responseId":"0619a56d9fed80853624df0c5c236c0e"}}
