{"type":"message","id":"6055136c","parentId":"3e887a45","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:04:36.926Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - when I run it manually, it works! So the `.env.tushare: Operation not permitted` error from cron might be due to cron running under a different user or a different environment. But wait - the cron entry shows `cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && /bin/bash scripts/cron_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh` which is running as my user. And the PATH fix I just made to `cron_python.sh` should have addressed the openclaw PATH issue.\n\nBut the `.env.tushare` error - when I ran manually it worked fine. \n\nSince the command succeeded just now, the cron job for today should have already executed and potentially succeeded. The current time is 21:04, and the cron runs at 09:35, so it already ran hours ago. When I checked the log earlier, it showed the error for today's run, but now that I've fixed the PATH issue in `cron_python.sh`, maybe the next execution will work properly.\n\nThe \"Operation not permitted\" error is puzzling since it worked when I ran it manually. I'm wondering if the Python framework version being used in cron might have sandbox restrictions applied, or if the process was already cached when it worked. Let me wait and see what happens with the next scheduled run.\n\nActually, I should focus on fixing the openclaw PATH issue in `cron_python.sh` and the config validation error instead. For the `.env.tushare` problem, the manual run succeeded with exit code 0, so it might be intermittent. I'm also noticing that `paper_profiles_morning_cron.log` shows a previous failure for 20260327 with exit code 2 — likely because the market was closed and merged signals weren't available. The cron job tries to run every day but exits with code 2 when there's no valid trading day, which gets recorded as a warning. The `.env.tushare` error might have been resolved once I fixed the PATH issue in `cron_python.sh`, so let me verify the other problems first.","thinkingSignature":"c6514167038aec1a248c874d7223d32eebb294bb6b4502f7bfaba4ab58cf903a"},{"type":"text","text":"手动跑竟然成功了——说明 `cron_python.sh` 的 PATH 修复可能也同时解决了 `.env.tushare` 的问题（之前 cron 里 PATH 不全可能导致某个中间状态异常）。现在处理第三个问题——`global_market_morning_0850.log` 的 Feishu config 错误：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1gnfcea5md16_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && /Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/bin/openclaw doctor --fix 2>&1 | tail -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55964,"output":563,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81547,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774875857314,"responseId":"0619a7d1f93881a9a1f023d5fd065833"}}
