{"type":"message","id":"9f88854e","parentId":"c093994b","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:09:30.384Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see - the probe guard suite only runs for defensive, balanced, and aggressive. But the control tower shows exit_tight, exit_dual, and alpha55 as having `missing_probe_guard`. \n\nThese three profiles (exit_tight, exit_dual, alpha55) don't have probe_guard configs set up in the cron. The control tower is expecting probe_guard for all profiles but only 3 of 8 have them configured.\n\nThis is a configuration gap - either:\n1. We need to create probe_guard configs for exit_tight, exit_dual, alpha55\n2. Or the control tower logic should not flag these as `missing_probe_guard` if the profile doesn't use probe_guard\n   \nI should check what these profiles actually are in the trading system to understand if they should have probe_guard coverage at all.","thinkingSignature":"27532dde1fd7e4f82c15893d8e2819cc99bcce48c9fba985457ad89ce11705e6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_48hg0fgawqjl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/strategy_probe_guard_defensive_v1.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_48hg0fgawqjl_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config -name \"strategy_probe_guard*\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":63601,"output":289,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876161172,"responseId":"0619a9017553c9e3213888d58cf85a17"}}
