{"type":"message","id":"3c8eff26","parentId":"f7a0f87e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:09:41.212Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue. The probe guard suite (`cron_close_review_v2.sh`) only runs probe guards for `defensive`, `balanced`, and `aggressive` - not for `exit_tight`, `exit_dual`, `alpha55`, `breadth_strict_oos`, `breadth_aggressive`.\n\nThe control tower is flagging `missing_probe_guard` for the profiles that don't have probe guard configs. These are different strategy types:\n- `exit_tight` and `exit_dual` are exit strategy profiles (they test different exit rules)\n- `alpha55` is a different strategy\n- `breadth_strict_oos` and `breadth_aggressive` are breadth-based strategies\n\n\n- The real issue is that the control tower shouldn't flag these as `missing_probe_guard` since they're not intended to have probe guard coverage - they're either experimental variants or use different guard mechanisms entirely. Looking at the HTML output, all 8 profiles are marked YELLOW, with aggressive being RED due to the NO_JOURNAL issue we already resolved. The probe guard is specifically designed for the 3 main paper trading profiles, so these others shouldn't be held to that same standard.","thinkingSignature":"b291195a7481fb69c1b66feb5b73a14247e2c972dfee7e8f8f0b9d95e95c348d"},{"type":"text","text":"看到了。\"策略与收益层\"有 8 个异常，我来分析每条的根因和是否需要修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zhgdc7x166b7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"missing_probe_guard\\|SHARPE_20D_BREACH\\|signal_stale_hold\\|signal_stale\\|POSITION_DRIFT\\|STALE_ALERT\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_control_tower_daily.py | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64296,"output":362,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89678,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":