{"type":"message","id":"5f4159eb","parentId":"4029a72e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:09:56.940Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the list of PROFILE_SLUGS: `defensive`, `balanced`, `aggressive`, `exit_dual`, `exit_tight`, `alpha55`, `breadth_strict_oos`, `breadth_aggressive`.\n\nThese 8 profiles are all being tracked in the \"策略与收益层\" table. But only 3 of them (`defensive`, `balanced`, `aggressive`) have probe_guard configs that run via cron.\n\nThe `missing_probe_guard` issue for `exit_tight`, `exit_dual`, and `alpha55` is because:\n1. The control tower checks if probe guard summary has entries for these profiles\n\n\n2. But only `defensive`, `balanced`, `aggressive` have probe_guard configs in `cron_close_review_v2.sh`\n\nSo the issue is: the control tower is checking ALL 8 profiles for probe_guard data, but the cron only generates probe_guard for 3 of them. This is a configuration gap. I need to understand the proper fix here - whether I should add probe_guard configs for the missing profiles or adjust what the control tower is checking for.","thinkingSignature":"06a7680ddb65e15a2707443340c85f3e1e33cb198d15fda5c3eaccf56764e99b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c01qdfry3uw8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '670,740p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_control_tower_daily.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65146,"output":296,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90462,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876187426,"responseId":"0619a91b4cf8948d596e95b5a9fa4267"}}
