{"type":"message","id":"eed630bc","parentId":"4283802c","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:11:02.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The `CURRENT_PAPER_SLUGS` includes `exit_dual`, `exit_tight`, `alpha55`, `breadth_strict_oos`, `breadth_aggressive`, and the three main profiles (`defensive`, `balanced`, `aggressive`).\n\nThe probe guard check (line 91-93) says: if the profile is in `CURRENT_PAPER_SLUGS` and there's no probe guard file, flag as `missing_probe_guard`. This was intentionally designed - all 8 profiles are expected to have probe guards.\n\nBut in reality, only 3 have probe guard configs that run in the cron. The other 5 don't have them set up.\n\n\nSo the fix is to add probe guard configurations for the missing profiles (`exit_dual`, `exit_tight`, `alpha55`, `breadth_strict_oos`, `breadth_aggressive`) and ensure they run on schedule, while also addressing the `SHARPE_20D_BREACH` on defensive and `signal_stale` issues on the breadth strategies. The `balanced` profile showing `none` as the issue but still marked YELLOW is worth investigating separately.\n\nThe `signal_stale` problem stems from the breadth strategies holding stale signals when the market's closed, and `SHARPE_20D_BREACH` on defensive means the 20-day Sharpe ratio has dropped below its threshold. Rather than getting sidetracked by the control tower regeneration, I should focus on what's actually actionable—setting up those missing probe guard configs is the real priority since it directly addresses why these profiles are flagged as YELLOW in the first place.","thinkingSignature":"8b8170e2fa824accbc55104adf17c2da36fb3e7e1fd75f07495fed8328c0a343"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_eru49amzlrzp_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"amber-cedar","timeout":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":72597,"output":395,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0