{"type":"message","id":"e320f50e","parentId":"8f2969e0","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:12:00.154Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to:\n1. Create probe_guard configs for exit_dual, exit_tight, alpha55, breadth_strict_oos, breadth_aggressive\n2. Add them to the cron_close_review_v2.sh\n\nFor the probe_guard config, I need to look at the structure. Each config has:\n- `strategy_id`\n- `profile_slug`\n- `profile_name`\n- `feishu` (same for all)\n- `thresholds`: paper_max_drawdown_pct, paper_20d_return_floor_pct, paper_20d_sharpe_floor, paper_avg_slippage_cap, paper_avg_turnover_cap, paper_position_deviation_cap, paper_missing_journal_records_cap, paper_error_trade_count_cap\n\n\n- `admission`: paper_observation_min_days, paper_observation_target_days, probe_capital_pct_min, probe_capital_pct_max\n\nNow I'm setting threshold values for each strategy. For exit_dual, exit_tight, and alpha55, I'll apply moderate conservative thresholds similar to the balanced profile since these are experimental variants that need protection without being overly restrictive. The breadth_strict_oos and breadth_aggressive strategies are more aggressive in positioning, so they need higher drawdown tolerance at 15% since they aim for 80% actual position. Looking at the current YELLOW status, the breadth strategies are already exceeding their max drawdown limits, so I need to calibrate these thresholds to match the actual risk they're taking on.","thinkingSignature":"f708343a49f1f0628c5487df26d46365011072f5f57f3d692282868632264d69"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ym5yqex0uuv6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '55,95p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/strategy_probe_guard_balanced_v1.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74920,"output":370,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100310,"cost":{"input":0,"ou