{"type":"message","id":"5e76d679","parentId":"c11c3627","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:14:09.248Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly. The aggressive RED issue is `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` with 12 planned orders and 0 journal records. This is the issue we fixed in the code, but the guard is still reporting it because:\n\n1. The guard is running on today's date (20260330)\n2. The aggressive account has `planned_orders: 12` but `journal_records: 0`\n3. The issue is that all 12 orders were blocked (because of the wrong `--strategy-max-dd-pct`)\n\nMy fix to `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` will prevent this from happening for future runs. But the current RED status is from the fact that the orders were generated (today is 20260330, the date_tag for the orders) and they were all blocked, so journal_records = 0 while planned_orders > 0.\n\n\nThe cron ran at 16:10, after the precheck at 09:20, which means my code fix wouldn't have been in effect for that earlier run. But actually, the real issue is that my fix changes how the account state is loaded for a given date, not when orders are generated—the orders were blocked because the account state had the wrong max drawdown percentage.\n\nLooking at the guard output for 20260330, it shows the halt reason is `strategy_max_drawdown_pct(24.5200) >= 10.0000`, which is the same 24.52% that came from `runtime_metrics[\"strategy_max_dd_pct\"]`. My fix switches this to use `state[\"drawdown_pct\"]` instead, but since the precheck already ran with the old logic, the orders for that date were already blocked before the fix could take effect.\n\nTomorrow (20260331) this should resolve itself—the control tower will regenerate with updated status if there are no planned orders for that date. I should also check whether the breadth signal_stale issue stems from the same problem.\n\nLooking at the `breadth_strict_oos_probe_guard` output would show if `missing_probe_guard` is what's triggering the signal_stale problem, but those files don't exist yet since the configs were only just created. Let me check if the panels have finished generating.","thinkingSignature":"0a159c75e6bea0b286cc531a97d01b3c9b613a41503e02740cddb6efe65ea775"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qh3eaa5rfelb_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"amber-cedar","timeout":30000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70993,"output":517,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96530,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876429987,"responseId":"0619aa0e09ce8566211c5f0e2cd5411f"}}
