<td>934977.27</td><td>-6.50%</td><td>-6.50%</td><td>none</td></tr><tr><td>balanced</td><td>YELLOW</td><td>observe</td><td>992050.33</td><td>-0.79%</td><td>-0.79%</td><td>none</td></tr><tr><td>defensive</td><td>YELLOW</td><td>cautious</td><td>993364.86</td><td>-0.66%</td><td>-0.66%</td><td>SHARPE_20D_BREACH</td></tr><tr><td>breadth_aggressive</td><td>YELLOW</td><td>signal_stale_hold</td><td>997608.93</td><td>-0.24%</td><td>-0.49%</td><td>signal_stale</td></tr><tr><td>breadth_strict_oos</td><td>YELLOW</td><td>signal_stale_hold</td><td>1005115.89</td><td>0.51%</td><td>-0.20%</td><td>signal_stale</td></tr><tr><td>alpha55</td><td>YELLOW</td><td>cautious</td><td>1000000.00</td><td>0.00%</td><td>0.00%</td><td>NO_ACTIVITY_DAY</td></tr></tbody></table>\n    </section>\n  </div>","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774876683968}}
{"type":"message","id":"4edbfe7c","parentId":"c1c883ea","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:18:23.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the state after the fix:\n\n1. **aggressive** - RED: `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` - This is the one I fixed earlier today (the live combo max_drawdown issue). But it's still RED because the RED status comes from the guard's own check - it still detects that there are planned orders (12) but no journal records. This is the correct behavior for the guard. The fix I made was for the future - so it won't happen again. But for today, the RED is correct because there were planned orders and no journal records. Actually, wait - let me re-read what happened. \n\nThe guard caught that 12 BUY orders were generated but none were actually executed due to the halt, which is why it's flagging `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` - the guard doesn't care that I fixed the underlying issue, it just sees that today had orders without any execution records.\n\nFor `exit_tight` and `exit_dual`, the `missing_probe_guard` warning disappeared and they're now showing `none` as expected. `alpha55` and `breadth_strict_oos` both had their probe guards added today and are now properly flagged with `NO_ACTIVITY_DAY` and `signal_stale` respectively. The `balanced` profile went from `none` to also showing `none` under the YELLOW status.\n\nThe remaining alerts are mostly informational or expected - `aggressive` has `NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS` which should resolve itself going forward since there won't be new orders without journal records, and `breadth_aggressive` shows `signal_stale` which is tied to its own separate monitoring. `defensive` has `SHARPE_20D_BREACH` which is legitimate. The only real lingering issue is `balanced` showing YELLOW with no specific reason, which appears to be a bug in the display logic.\n\nLooking at `alpha55`, it went from `missing_probe_guard` to `cautious` mode with `NO_ACTIVITY_DAY` - so it's functioning correctly now. The remaining items are mostly noise: `defensive` with a legitimate Sharpe breach, the breadth-related stale signals tied to the `POSITION_DRIFT_CRITICAL` issue from breadth_strict_oos, and `aggressive`'s journal/planned orders issue. The most actionable fix is that `balanced` shouldn't be yellow at all.\n\nBut wait, the nav values are shifting between renders - balanced went from 994607.97 to 992050.33, and defensive from 994709.26 to 993364.86. This is because multiple cron jobs are running simultaneously, each pulling the latest data and overwriting files, which is causing inconsistent readings across the control tower.","thinkingSignature":"ddc0a93d453819b37d2e366472484a7326a81fd0733ebf93e1fd89257d47431c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2iqau74vp0fv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"breadth_strict_oos\\|POSITION_DRIFT\\|STALE_ALERT\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_strategy_performance_panel.py | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":86900,"output":657,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112577,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876683983,"responseId":"0619ab0cdc191e03fa2c20946adf68ca"}}
