{"type":"message","id":"6557d614","parentId":"31ac547e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:18:27.941Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `signal_stale` is from the breadth alert, not from the probe guard. Let me look at how `breadth_strict_oos` and `breadth_aggressive` get their issue codes in the performance panel.","thinkingSignature":"fa3aaf69c6acd86b14c341b206eb9c088dee6bc98c46c808b94d5c0f7f74f6ce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_udn2n4mf0ufb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '225,280p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_strategy_performance_panel.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87575,"output":109,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112704,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876703555,"responseId":"0619ab1f07017561a611d008713eec64"}}
{"type":"message","id":"42440485","parentId":"6557d614","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:18:28.053Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_udn2n4mf0ufb_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"if prev_total_value is not None:\n            day_pnl = round(total_value - prev_total_value, 2)\n        prev_total_value = total_value\n        breadth_curve.append(\n            {\n                \"date\": str(item.get(\"date\", \"\")),\n                \"nav\": round(total_value, 2),\n                \"drawdown_pct\": latest_drawdown_pct,\n            }\n        )\n\n    total_return_pct = round((latest_nav_ratio - 1.0) * 100.0, 2) if latest_nav_ratio > 0 else 0.0\n    reasons: list[str] = []\n    detail_parts: list[str] = []\n    status = \"GREEN\"\n    status_label = \"GREEN\"\n    if bool(breadth_summary.get(\"signal_stale\", False)):\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        status_label = \"STALE\"\n        reasons.append(\"signal_stale\")\n    age_hours = file_age_hours(summary_path)\n    status, status_label, reasons = apply_stale_override(status, status_label, reasons, age_hours)\n    freshness_text, _ = freshness_label(age_hours)\n\n    stale_reason = str(breadth_summary.get(\"signal_stale_reason\") or \"\").strip()\n    if stale_reason:\n        detail_parts.append(stale_reason)\n\n    return {\n        \"group\": spec[\"group\"],\n        \"group_label\": spec[\"group_label\"],\n        \"profile_slug\": str(breadth_summary.get(\"slug\") or profile_slug),\n        \"profile_name\": str(spec[\"name\"]),\n        \"short_name\": str(spec.get(\"short_name\") or spec[\"name\"]),\n        \"date_tag\": str(breadth_summary.get(\"signal_date\") or \"\"),\n        \"status\": status,\n        \"status_label\": status_label,\n        \"tomorrow_mode\": str(breadth_summary.get(\"execution_status\") or \"experimental\"),\n        \"nav\": round(latest_total_value, 2),\n        \"total_return_pct\": total_return_pct,\n        \"day_pnl\": day_pnl,\n        \"drawdown_pct\": latest_drawdown_pct,\n        \"cash\": round(parse_float(breadth_summary.get(\"cash\"), 0.0), 2),\n        \"market_value\": round(parse_float(breadth_summary.get(\"market_value\"), 0.0), 2),\n        \"position_count\": int(breadth_summary.get(\"position_count\", 0) or 0),\n        \"today_trade_count\": int(len(breadth_summary.get(\"buy_list\", [])) + len(breadth_summary.get(\"sell_list\", []))),\n        \"issue_codes\": \", \".join(reasons) if reasons else \"none\",\n        \"curve\": breadth_curve,\n        \"freshness\": freshness_text,\n        \"file_updated_at\": datetime.fromtimestamp(summary_path.stat().st_mtime).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\") if summary_path.exists() else \"-\",\n        \"status_reason\": \" | \".join(detail_parts) if detail_parts else (\", \".join(reasons) if reasons else \"ok\"),\n        \"guard_present\": False,\n    }\n\n\ndef build_rows() -> list[dict[str, Any]]:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":35,"aggregated":"if prev_total_value is not None:\n            day_pnl = round(total_value - prev_total_value, 2)\n        prev_total_value = total_value\n        breadth_curve.append(\n            {\n                \"date\": str(item.get(\"date\", \"\")),\n                \"nav\": round(total_value, 2),\n                \"drawdown_pct\": latest_drawdown_pct,\n            }\n        )\n\n    total_return_pct = round((latest_nav_ratio - 1.0) * 100.0, 2) if latest_nav_ratio > 0 else 0.0\n    reasons: list[str] = []\n    detail_parts: list[str] = []\n    status = \"GREEN\"\n    status_label = \"GREEN\"\n    if bool(breadth_summary.get(\"signal_stale\", False)):\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        status_label = \"STALE\"\n        reasons.append(\"signal_stale\")\n    age_hours = file_age_hours(summary_path)\n    status, status_label, reasons = apply_stale_override(status, status_label, reasons, age_hours)\n    freshness_text, _ = freshness_label(age_hours)\n\n    stale_reason = str(breadth_summary.get(\"signal_stale_reason\") or \"\").strip()\n    if stale_reason:\n        detail_parts.append(stale_reason)\n\n    return {\n        \"group\": spec[\"group\"],\n        \"group_label\": spec[\"group_label\"],\n        \"profile_slug\": str(breadth_summary.get(\"slug\") or profile_slug),\n        \"profile_name\": str(spec[\"name\"]),\n        \"short_name\": str(spec.get(\"short_name\") or spec[\"name\"]),\n        \"date_tag\": str(breadth_summary.get(\"signal_date\") or \"\"),\n        \"status\": status,\n        \"status_label\": status_label,\n        \"tomorrow_mode\": str(breadth_summary.get(\"execution_status\") or \"experimental\"),\n        \"nav\": round(latest_total_value, 2),\n        \"total_return_pct\": total_return_pct,\n        \"day_pnl\": day_pnl,\n        \"drawdown_pct\": latest_drawdown_pct,\n        \"cash\": round(parse_float(breadth_summary.get(\"cash\"), 0.0), 2),\n        \"market_value\": round(parse_float(breadth_summary.get(\"market_value\"), 0.0), 2),\n        \"position_count\": int(breadth_summary.get(\"position_count\", 0) or 0),\n        \"today_trade_count\": int(len(breadth_summary.get(\"buy_list\", [])) + len(breadth_summary.get(\"sell_list\", []))),\n        \"issue_codes\": \", \".join(reasons) if reasons else \"none\",\n        \"curve\": breadth_curve,\n        \"freshness\": freshness_text,\n        \"file_updated_at\": datetime.fromtimestamp(summary_path.stat().st_mtime).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\") if summary_path.exists() else \"-\",\n        \"status_reason\": \" | \".join(detail_parts) if detail_parts else (\", \".join(reasons) if reasons else \"ok\"),\n        \"guard_present\": False,\n    }\n\n\ndef build_rows() -> list[dict[str, Any]]:","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774876708038}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f9b1227","parentId":"42440485","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:18:55.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that for breadth profiles, the `signal_stale` issue comes from `breadth_summary.get(\"signal_stale\")`. This is read from the `breadth_strict_oos_alert_state.json` (or similar breadth summary). \n\nThe `signal_stale` is set by the breadth alert system, not by the probe guard. This is a separate system tracking whether the breadth signal is fresh.\n\nFor `breadth_aggressive`, the signal is also `signal_stale`. This means the breadth signal for both breadth profiles is stale.\n\nThe `POSITION_DRIFT_CRITICAL`告警 from earlier is also from the breadth alert state. The issue is that the breadth strategy has 80% target position but only 31% actual, causing a -48.85% drift. \n\nThe signal_stale condition suggests the breadth signal hasn't been refreshed recently. The cron job `cron_breadth_strict_oos_paper.sh` runs at 09:15 on trading days, and I saw the latest breadth_strict_oos_paper_latest.json was generated at 09:16:32 today. Since this is a breadth-specific alert state rather than a probe guard issue, it's being flagged by the breadth monitoring system itself. Looking at the cron jobs more carefully, the breadth scripts run at 09:15 on trading days, which explains why the signal data is current up to that point. The signal_stale flag is likely being set because the current time (21:17) is far past the morning execution window, so the breadth strategy has been in signal_stale_hold mode throughout the day.\n\nFor the YELLOW statuses in the control tower, most of the missing_probe_guard issues have been resolved by adding probe guard configs and regenerating today. The aggressive guard correctly flags NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS as expected, while balanced and breadth_aggressive are properly showing YELLOW with signal_stale since their stale signals are legitimate conditions that don't require immediate action.\n\nThe remaining YELLOW statuses are all valid business concerns rather than system bugs: defensive has a Sharpe breach which is real, breadth_strict_oos is in a legitimate signal_stale_hold mode, and alpha55 shows NO_ACTIVITY_DAY which is expected behavior. There's also a confirmed bug where balanced shows YELLOW but has no issue code—the probe guard correctly returns GREEN but the performance panel displays it as YELLOW, which I should fix.\n\nLooking at the balanced probe guard data, it shows GREEN status, yet the control tower displays YELLOW for balanced. The issue codes show \"none\" which should indicate GREEN, so there's likely a stale file or override happening somewhere in the control tower logic.\n\nActually, wait—I'm seeing stale data in the control tower. The aggressive nav is showing 996111.32, which is from 2026-03-30, but I generated fresh control tower data at 21:17 today (2026-03-30). The HTML page at http://127.0.0.1:3847/control_tower_daily_latest.html might be serving old cached data instead of my freshly generated output.\n\nThe real question is whether this is a data issue or a caching problem—the control tower file itself shows the updated nav values, but the web page might not be reflecting these changes. Let me focus on the actual problems I can fix: the numpy.float64 error is resolved, and I've added the missing probe guard configs. The aggressive RED alert about missing journals with planned orders should self-resolve now that I fixed the underlying issue preventing new orders from generating without corresponding journal entries. For the balanced display bug, I need to determine if it's actually a bug or just stale cached data.","thinkingSignature":"55b717dda27f7a82a13117de66ee02380a9e7e946671b21aac71a5e4e645c54d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ao22ajfjen28_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"STATUS_ORDER\\|status_rank\\|guard_status.*YELLOW\\|status == \\\"YELLOW\\\"\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_strategy_performance_panel.py | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":88360,"output":841,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114221,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876708054,"responseId":"0619ab24b971aa324c37de7a55f2bdcf"}}
