{"type":"message","id":"a424f81f","parentId":"ba007606","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:19:28.597Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The balanced probe guard returns `status: \"YELLOW\"` with `issues: []`. So the guard itself is returning YELLOW even with no issues. Let me look at why.\n\nLooking at the guard code, the guard could be returning YELLOW because of:\n- `paper_20d_sharpe_floor` breach\n- `paper_position_deviation_cap` breach\n- Other thresholds\n\nBut looking at the stats: `trailing_20d_sharpe: 0.0`. The threshold for balanced is `paper_20d_sharpe_floor: 0.0`. Since 0.0 < 0.0 would be False (0.0 is not less than 0.0), this shouldn't trigger.\n\n\nI need to examine the full set of stats from the balanced guard report to understand what's actually causing the YELLOW status.","thinkingSignature":"e2bc8da898ca9248109001e14946e80ec7c9d188074815efa0ec12f61c1184b1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f9cfts6vye1f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_balanced_probe_guard_latest.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('stats', {}), indent=2))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90281,"output":267,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115568,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876751400,"responseId":"0619ab4f358cc65288f847591ec9ef14"}}
