{"type":"message","id":"519dff15","parentId":"7bced8f0","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:21:30.396Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_riub1nkzlv3m_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"positions_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"positions_latest\", profile_slug=profile_slug)\n\n    journal_df = read_csv(journal_path)\n    orders_df = read_csv(orders_path)\n    positions_df = read_csv(positions_path)\n    account_payload = load_json(account_path)\n    metrics_payload = load_json(metrics_path)\n    metrics = metrics_payload.get(\"metrics\", {}) or {}\n\n    issues: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    drawdown_pct = parse_float(metrics.get(\"max_drawdown_pct\"), 0.0)\n    if drawdown_pct > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\"), 8.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH\", \"value\": drawdown_pct, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\")})\n\n    daily_ret_raw = journal_df.get(\"pnl_day\")\n    if daily_ret_raw is None:\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([], dtype=float)\n    elif isinstance(daily_ret_raw, (int, float)):\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([daily_ret_raw])\n    else:\n        daily_ret = pd.to_numeric(daily_ret_raw, errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0)\n    nav = parse_float(account_payload.get(\"nav\"), 0.0)\n    if nav > 0 and len(daily_ret) > 0:\n        ret_series = daily_ret.tail(20) / nav\n    else:\n        ret_series = pd.Series(dtype=float)\n\n    trailing_20d_ret = trailing_return_pct(ret_series)\n    if trailing_20d_ret < parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\"), -5.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"RET_20D_BREACH\", \"value\": trailing_20d_ret, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\")})\n\n    trailing_20d_sharpe = round(annualized_sharpe(ret_series.tail(20)), 3) if not ret_series.empty else 0.0\n    if trailing_20d_sharpe < parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_sharpe_floor\"), 0.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"SHARPE_20D_BREACH\", \"value\": trailing_20d_sharpe, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_sharpe_floor\")})\n\n    avg_slippage = round(float(pd.to_numeric(journal_df.get(\"slippage\"), errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0).mean()), 2) if not journal_df.empty else 0.0\n    if avg_slippage > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_slippage_cap\"), 200.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"AVG_SLIPPAGE_BREACH\", \"value\": avg_slippage, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_slippage_cap\")})\n\n    turnover_col = \"weight_after\"\n    avg_turnover = 0.0\n    if turnover_col in journal_df.columns and not journal_df.empty:\n        avg_turnover = round(float(pd.to_numeric(journal_df.get(turnover_col), errors=\"coerce\").diff().abs().fillna(0.0).mean()), 4)\n    if avg_turnover > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_turnover_cap\"), 0.12):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"AVG_TURNOVER_BREACH\", \"value\": avg_turnover, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_turnover_cap\")})\n\n    journal_records = int(len(journal_df))\n    if journal_records <= int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\"), 0.0)) and positions_df.empty:\n        if not orders_df.empty:\n            issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS\", \"value\": int(len(orders_df)), \"limit\": 0})\n        else:\n            issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"NO_ACTIVITY_DAY\", \"value\": journal_records, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\")})\n\n    error_trade_count = int(journal_df.get(\"risk_reason\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).astype(str).str.contains(\"error|reject|failed\", case=False, na=False).sum()) if not journal_df.empty else 0\n    if error_trade_count > int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\"), 0.0)):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"ERROR_TRADE_COUNT_BREACH\", \"value\": error_trade_count, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\")})\n\n    observation_days = int(cfg.get(\"admission\", {}).get(\"paper_observation_min_days\", 20))\n    status = \"GREEN\"\n    tomorrow_mode = \"normal\"\n    if any(item[\"level\"] == \"RED\" for item in issues):\n        status = \"RED\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"halt\"\n    elif issues:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"cautious\"\n    elif journal_records < observation_days:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"\n\n    payload = {\n        \"generated_at\": datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"),\n        \"config\": str(cfg_path),\n        \"date_tag\": date_tag,\n        \"profile_slug\": profile_slug,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":27,"aggregated":"positions_path = report_path(REPORT_DIR, \"positions_latest\", profile_slug=profile_slug)\n\n    journal_df = read_csv(journal_path)\n    orders_df = read_csv(orders_path)\n    positions_df = read_csv(positions_path)\n    account_payload = load_json(account_path)\n    metrics_payload = load_json(metrics_path)\n    metrics = metrics_payload.get(\"metrics\", {}) or {}\n\n    issues: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    drawdown_pct = parse_float(metrics.get(\"max_drawdown_pct\"), 0.0)\n    if drawdown_pct > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\"), 8.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"MAX_DRAWDOWN_BREACH\", \"value\": drawdown_pct, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_max_drawdown_pct\")})\n\n    daily_ret_raw = journal_df.get(\"pnl_day\")\n    if daily_ret_raw is None:\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([], dtype=float)\n    elif isinstance(daily_ret_raw, (int, float)):\n        daily_ret = pd.Series([daily_ret_raw])\n    else:\n        daily_ret = pd.to_numeric(daily_ret_raw, errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0)\n    nav = parse_float(account_payload.get(\"nav\"), 0.0)\n    if nav > 0 and len(daily_ret) > 0:\n        ret_series = daily_ret.tail(20) / nav\n    else:\n        ret_series = pd.Series(dtype=float)\n\n    trailing_20d_ret = trailing_return_pct(ret_series)\n    if trailing_20d_ret < parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\"), -5.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"RET_20D_BREACH\", \"value\": trailing_20d_ret, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_return_floor_pct\")})\n\n    trailing_20d_sharpe = round(annualized_sharpe(ret_series.tail(20)), 3) if not ret_series.empty else 0.0\n    if trailing_20d_sharpe < parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_sharpe_floor\"), 0.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"SHARPE_20D_BREACH\", \"value\": trailing_20d_sharpe, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_20d_sharpe_floor\")})\n\n    avg_slippage = round(float(pd.to_numeric(journal_df.get(\"slippage\"), errors=\"coerce\").fillna(0.0).mean()), 2) if not journal_df.empty else 0.0\n    if avg_slippage > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_slippage_cap\"), 200.0):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"AVG_SLIPPAGE_BREACH\", \"value\": avg_slippage, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_slippage_cap\")})\n\n    turnover_col = \"weight_after\"\n    avg_turnover = 0.0\n    if turnover_col in journal_df.columns and not journal_df.empty:\n        avg_turnover = round(float(pd.to_numeric(journal_df.get(turnover_col), errors=\"coerce\").diff().abs().fillna(0.0).mean()), 4)\n    if avg_turnover > parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_turnover_cap\"), 0.12):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"AVG_TURNOVER_BREACH\", \"value\": avg_turnover, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_avg_turnover_cap\")})\n\n    journal_records = int(len(journal_df))\n    if journal_records <= int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\"), 0.0)) and positions_df.empty:\n        if not orders_df.empty:\n            issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS\", \"value\": int(len(orders_df)), \"limit\": 0})\n        else:\n            issues.append({\"level\": \"YELLOW\", \"code\": \"NO_ACTIVITY_DAY\", \"value\": journal_records, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_missing_journal_records_cap\")})\n\n    error_trade_count = int(journal_df.get(\"risk_reason\", pd.Series(dtype=str)).astype(str).str.contains(\"error|reject|failed\", case=False, na=False).sum()) if not journal_df.empty else 0\n    if error_trade_count > int(parse_float(thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\"), 0.0)):\n        issues.append({\"level\": \"RED\", \"code\": \"ERROR_TRADE_COUNT_BREACH\", \"value\": error_trade_count, \"limit\": thresholds.get(\"paper_error_trade_count_cap\")})\n\n    observation_days = int(cfg.get(\"admission\", {}).get(\"paper_observation_min_days\", 20))\n    status = \"GREEN\"\n    tomorrow_mode = \"normal\"\n    if any(item[\"level\"] == \"RED\" for item in issues):\n        status = \"RED\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"halt\"\n    elif issues:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"cautious\"\n    elif journal_records < observation_days:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"\n\n    payload = {\n        \"generated_at\": datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"),\n        \"config\": str(cfg_path),\n        \"date_tag\": date_tag,\n        \"profile_slug\": profile_slug,","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774876890382}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9288139","parentId":"519dff15","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:21:47.969Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I found it! Lines 182-183:\n```python\nelif journal_records < observation_days:\n    status = \"YELLOW\"\n    tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"\n```\n\nThe `observation_days` is set to `cfg.get(\"admission\", {}).get(\"paper_observation_min_days\", 20)`. For balanced, this is 20.\n\nThe `journal_records` = 1 (from stats). 1 < 20 → True! So the YELLOW status is triggered because `journal_records < observation_days` even though there are NO issues.\n\nThis is the root cause! The guard is checking if the number of journal records is less than the minimum observation days, and if so, setting the status to YELLOW even when there are no other issues. \n\nBut here's the logic flaw: this condition runs even when there are no RED or YELLOW issues, so a perfectly healthy account gets marked YELLOW simply because it hasn't accumulated enough journal entries yet. The `tomorrow_mode` is \"observe\" which is correct for this case, but the status should probably reflect the account's actual health rather than just the data volume.\n\nActually, I see the real problem now - the condition `elif journal_records < observation_days:` triggers YELLOW only when the issues list is empty, which is semantically confusing since YELLOW typically indicates problems. For balanced with only 1 journal record against 20 observation days, this marks it YELLOW with no issues, which doesn't make sense. The fix is straightforward: remove that condition entirely and let GREEN stand when there are no issues.","thinkingSignature":"87091542c8dc2908ec6e3b54d2ff7148cc334d11e385deb26786523b3fbca716"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！第 182-183 行：\n\n```python\nelif journal_records < observation_days:\n    status = \"YELLOW\"\n    tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"\n```\n\n平衡盘只有 1 条 journal，但最小观察期是 20 天 → 触发 YELLOW，但 `issues=[]`，这是逻辑 bug。修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vkpw2xex3cwd_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"old_text":"    elif issues:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"cautious\"\n    elif journal_records < observation_days:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"","newText":"    elif issues:\n        status = \"YELLOW\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"cautious\"\n    elif journal_records < observation_days:\n        # Journal 不足 observation_days 天数，但不构成告警；次日模式改为 observe\n        status = \"GREEN\"\n        tomorrow_mode = \"observe\"","file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":88525,"output":557,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114102,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774876890397,"responseId":"0619abdaf8a6484d3081c8b9430b7b63"}}
