{"type":"message","id":"de049668","parentId":"5581fdca","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:22:50.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The control tower is now much cleaner:\n\nBefore (8 items):\n1. aggressive → RED: NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS ✅\n2. exit_tight → YELLOW: missing_probe_guard ✅ FIXED\n3. exit_dual → YELLOW: missing_probe_guard ✅ FIXED\n4. balanced → YELLOW: none ✅ FIXED\n5. defensive → YELLOW: SHARPE_20D_BREACH ✅ (legitimate)\n6. breadth_aggressive → YELLOW: signal_stale ✅ (legitimate)\n7. breadth_strict_oos → YELLOW: signal_stale ✅ (legitimate)\n\n\n8. alpha55 → YELLOW: missing_probe_guard ✅ FIXED\n\nAfter (8 items):\n1. aggressive → RED: NO_JOURNAL_WITH_PLANNED_ORDERS ✅ (legitimate - yesterday's issue)\n2. defensive → YELLOW: SHARPE_20D_BREACH ✅ (legitimate business alert)\n3. breadth_aggressive → YELLOW: signal_stale ✅ (legitimate)\n4. breadth_strict_oos → YELLOW: signal_stale ✅ (legitimate)\n5. alpha55 → YELLOW: NO_ACTIVITY_DAY ✅ (business alert - NO journal records today, no planned orders)\n\nThe remaining items are all legitimate business alerts rather than system issues, with a couple still showing signal_stale as expected.\n\nFor aggressive, this RED status from yesterday's issue will clear on the next trading day when new orders generate with journal records, so there's nothing to fix there. The core problems are all resolved—the five missing probe guard configs are now in place, the observation period logic bug is fixed, the numpy.float64 fillna issue is patched, and the cron environment has the right PATH configured.","thinkingSignature":"4092e38e1d04e95844766324832d444742b38659067d3ca1ce200138e79df5e5"},{"type":"text","text":"刷新完成。现在提交修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r4yclr72ojjq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && git add \\\n  quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_probe_guard.py \\\n  quant_projects/perso