{"type":"message","id":"78817796","parentId":"da488d53","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:39:35.453Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the situation. Let me analyze:\n\n**Backtest vs Paper Trading gap analysis:**\n\n**Backtest (回测) vs Reality:**\n\nThe stable strategy (Qlib breadth + turnover hardcap relaxed) shows backtest from 2015-2026:\n- 年化: 55.07%\n- 最大回撤: 24.89%\n- 夏普: 2.794\n\nBut the paper trading results show much worse or just neutral:\n\n**Aggressive:**\n- Backtest: 55.07% annualized\n- Paper trading: -0.39% (since March 19, ~10 days)\n\n\n- Issue: 12 orders blocked by the halt mechanism before trading even started, and positions were fully liquidated on March 20\n\n**Balanced:**\n- Backtest: Balanced 12% strategy\n- Paper trading: -0.79% with only 3 holdings and minimal activity—just one sell on March 27\n- Issue: Multiple halt conditions blocking order execution\n\n**Defensive:**\n- Backtest: Defensive 8% strategy\n- Paper trading: -0.66% with 2 holdings and no new positions being added\n\n**Exit_dual and Exit_tight:**\nBoth showing severe drawdowns around -6.5%, holding 3 and 1 positions respectively after exiting on March 25-26 when stop-losses triggered\n\n**Core Problem:**\nThe halt mechanism was catching orders with a too-tight threshold, and once positions were stopped out on March 20, the market conditions shifted unfavorably, preventing new positions from being established.\n\n**Why Paper Underperforms Backtest:**\nThe strategy stopped out at exactly the wrong time (March 20), missing the recovery rally from March 21-25. Additionally, the halt mechanism was misinterpreting the historical backtest drawdown metric (24.52%) as a live trading signal, when it actually represents cumulative drawdown from an earlier period in the backtest itself.\n\nThere's also a timing mismatch—the breadth_strict_oos strategy is still using signals from March 3, which are now 27 days stale, meaning it hasn't captured any of the recent market recovery.\n\nTo improve the paper trading performance going forward, I should verify the halt mechanism is correctly applying the paper account's own drawdown rather than the historical backtest metric, confirm whether new signals have started coming through for the aggressive and balanced strategies, and assess whether the breadth_strict_oos strategy needs to refresh its signal generation to become actionable again.","thinkingSignature":"712179be8f274f712fcbe0be67e432c3f39c9420650814d1e71d6e01aea07358"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2u60xosxjolj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_aggressive_orders_v1_20260330.csv 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"---\"; cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_defensive_orders_v1_20260330.csv 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"---\"; cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_balanced_orders_v1_20260330.csv 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93886,"output":680,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119586,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774877949202,"responseId":"0619affd8ec63328708d1ca998910b0b"}}
