{"type":"message","id":"b2e53d0c","parentId":"f4c58033","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:40:05.125Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the FULL picture. The problem is clear:\n\n**All 12 BUY orders are blocked by `strategy_max_drawdown_pct(24.5100) >= 10.0000`** - this is the same root cause we already fixed. The fix hasn't been applied to this system's run_live_execution_v1.py yet (it's a different pipeline).\n\nSo the real issues are:\n\n1. **The halt mechanism is still using live combo DD (24.51%) instead of paper account DD** - this fix was only applied to `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` but the orders still show the old block reason. Wait... but we just fixed `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py`. \n\nThe orders are showing the old block reason, which means our fix to `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` changed `--strategy-max-dd-pct` but this is a separate issue - the blocking is happening in `run_live_execution_v1.py` based on `runtime_risk_state`. Looking at the orders pipeline, the prepare step reads from runtime_risk_state which has `strategy_max_dd_pct=24.51%`, then apply_risk checks it, and this is where the block happens. The fix we applied to `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` must have addressed the wrong layer in the pipeline.\n\nWait, let me trace this more carefully. The paper orders pipeline feeds into `apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py`, not the live execution path. So `run_live_execution_v1.py` uses the paper orders as inputs and still has the bug where it's checking the wrong dd_pct value.\n\nBut the real issue is that the orders generated by `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` still show the old 24.5100% value even after my fix - that's because the execution flow is controlled by `run_live_execution_v1.py` which reads from `runtime_risk_state` (containing the live combo dd), not the paper-specific dd value that I corrected. So I need to verify whether `run_live_execution_v1.py` is using the paper or live combo dd_pct to understand where the actual blocking logic lives. I see that `apply_risk_to_merged_signals.py` checks `args.strategy_max_dd_pct` as a gate for blocking orders, so I need to trace back where this parameter gets set in `run_live_execution_v1.py` to understand if it's using the hardcoded 10% threshold or pulling from somewhere else.","thinkingSignature":"d423523e01a203717a1e78f33ca6454e3882f0fedccc6466be622aa62d241245"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_adx28wll7y2t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"strategy_max_dd_pct\\|strategy-max-dd-pct\\|halt_new_buy\\|hard_stop\\|strategy_max_dd\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_live_execution_v1.py | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90287,"output":613,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115920,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774877975587,"responseId":"0619b017e81b6b33c3cf4c98fdedcb65"}}
