{"type":"message","id":"214e7233","parentId":"125640e3","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:50:06.941Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e2w7x1ayvfjc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nA股全量ML因子增强训练\n使用新下载的A股全量数据 (tushare_a_all) 进行特征工程和模型训练\n\"\"\"\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport json\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\n# 配置\nDATA_DIR = Path(\"data/tushare_a_all\")\nOUTPUT_DIR = Path(\"data/ml_dataset_full\")\nMODEL_OUTPUT_DIR = Path(\"models\")\nREPORTS_DIR = Path(\"research/reports\")\n\n# 日期范围\nTRAIN_START = \"2019-01-01\"\nTRAIN_END = \"2024-12-31\"\nTEST_START = \"2025-01-01\"\nTEST_END = \"2026-03-10\"\n\ndef load_and_preprocess():\n    \"\"\"加载并预处理A股全量数据\"\"\"\n    print(\"正在加载A股全量数据...\")\n    merged_path = DATA_DIR / \"a_stock_daily_merged.csv\"\n    \n    # 分块读取大文件\n    chunks = []\n    for chunk in pd.read_csv(merged_path, chunksize=100000):\n        chunks.append(chunk)\n    df = pd.concat(chunks, ignore_index=True)\n    \n    print(f\"原始数据行数: {len(df):,}\")\n    \n    # 转换日期\n    df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['trade_date'].astype(str), format='%Y%m%d', errors='coerce')\n    df = df.dropna(subset=['date', 'ts_code'])\n    df = df.sort_values(['ts_code', 'date']).reset_index(drop=True)\n    \n    print(f\"清洗后数据行数: {len(df):,}\")\n    print(f\"股票数: {df['ts_code'].nunique()}\")\n    print(f\"日期范围: {df['date'].min()} ~ {df['date'].max()}\")\n    \n    return df\n\ndef build_features(df):"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nA股全量ML因子增强训练\n使用新下载的A股全量数据 (tushare_a_all) 进行特征工程和模型训练\n\"\"\"\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport json\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\n# 配置\nDATA_DIR = Path(\"data/tushare_a_all\")\nOUTPUT_DIR = Path(\"data/ml_dataset_full\")\nMODEL_OUTPUT_DIR = Path(\"models\")\nREPORTS_DIR = Path(\"research/reports\")\n\n# 日期范围\nTRAIN_START = \"2019-01-01\"\nTRAIN_END = \"2024-12-31\"\nTEST_START = \"2025-01-01\"\nTEST_END = \"2026-03-10\"\n\ndef load_and_preprocess():\n    \"\"\"加载并预处理A股全量数据\"\"\"\n    print(\"正在加载A股全量数据...\")\n    merged_path = DATA_DIR / \"a_stock_daily_merged.csv\"\n    \n    # 分块读取大文件\n    chunks = []\n    for chunk in pd.read_csv(merged_path, chunksize=100000):\n        chunks.append(chunk)\n    df = pd.concat(chunks, ignore_index=True)\n    \n    print(f\"原始数据行数: {len(df):,}\")\n    \n    # 转换日期\n    df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['trade_date'].astype(str), format='%Y%m%d', errors='coerce')\n    df = df.dropna(subset=['date', 'ts_code'])\n    df = df.sort_values(['ts_code', 'date']).reset_index(drop=True)\n    \n    print(f\"清洗后数据行数: {len(df):,}\")\n    print(f\"股票数: {df['ts_code'].nunique()}\")\n    print(f\"日期范围: {df['date'].min()} ~ {df['date'].max()}\")\n    \n    return df\n\ndef build_features(df):","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774878606927}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e285426","parentId":"214e7233","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:50:18.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - `train_ml_factors_all_a.py` loads data from `data/tushare_a_all/a_stock_daily_merged.csv`. But the data we have in Qlib (refreshed from tushare) is in the qlib format in `/Users/ling/.qlib/qlib_data/`. \n\nThe issue is that:\n1. The predictions stop at 2026-03-10 (in the ml_predictions.csv file, we see the last date is 2026-03-03, not 03-10)\n2. The train_ml_factors_all_a.py trains from scratch using data in `data/tushare_a_all/`\n\n\n3. The last Qlib update run on 03-30 downloaded tushare data for 03-24 through 03-30, but the predictions file is still at 03-03\n\nSo the pipeline is: fresh tushare data gets downloaded to Qlib, then predictions need to be regenerated from the full training pipeline, which is expensive since it retrains the model from scratch. The core problem is that the prediction generation depends on reloading the full training dataset, which is time-intensive. Let me look at the cron script for the daily breadth job to understand the proper workflow and whether there's a lightweight prediction update option.","thinkingSignature":"4fcce349623fc62d940473715b862f5d3ab399901a91f36aa9ac6c5a4eb088f3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8alkimhutbv4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"train_ml\\|predictions\\|ml_predictions\\|tushare_to_qlib\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_daily_quant_analysis.sh 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8alkimhutbv4_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_daily_quant_analysis.sh 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65932,"output":408,"cacheRead":25020,"cacheWrite":