{"type":"message","id":"8ef5d839","parentId":"08943cc4","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:50:33.484Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5ydk1jp8442h_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"PROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDATA_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\" / \"ml_dataset_full\"\nPREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions.csv\"\nLIVE_PREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions_live_latest.csv\"\nFEATURES_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_features_full.csv\"\nMAX_SIGNAL_LAG_DAYS = 2\nTODAY_STR = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\nTODAY_ISO = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n\n\ndef append_history_records(summary: dict, slug: str) -> dict:\n    csv_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.csv\"\n    jsonl_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.jsonl\"\n    nav_history = summary.get(\"nav_history\", []) or []\n    compact_history: list[dict] = []\n    seen_markers: set[tuple[str, float, float]] = set()\n    for item in nav_history:\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        marker = (str(item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\")), nav, cash)\n        if marker in seen_markers:\n            continue\n        seen_markers.add(marker)\n        compact_history.append(item)\n    nav_history = compact_history\n    records: list[dict] = []\n    for idx, item in enumerate(nav_history):\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        total_value = round(nav * float(summary.get(\"paper_capital\", 0.0)), 2)\n        market_value = round(total_value - cash, 2)\n        records.append(\n            {\n                \"generated_at\": f\"{summary.get('generated_at')}#{idx+1}\",\n                \"signal_date\": item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\"),\n                \"nav\": nav,\n                \"total_value\": total_value,\n                \"cash\": cash,\n                \"market_value\": market_value,\n                \"position_count\": int(summary.get(\"position_count\", 0) or 0),"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"PROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDATA_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\" / \"ml_dataset_full\"\nPREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions.csv\"\nLIVE_PREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions_live_latest.csv\"\nFEATURES_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_features_full.csv\"\nMAX_SIGNAL_LAG_DAYS = 2\nTODAY_STR = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\nTODAY_ISO = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n\n\ndef append_history_records(summary: dict, slug: str) -> dict:\n    csv_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.csv\"\n    jsonl_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.jsonl\"\n    nav_history = summary.get(\"nav_history\", []) or []\n    compact_history: list[dict] = []\n    seen_markers: set[tuple[str, float, float]] = set()\n    for item in nav_history:\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        marker = (str(item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\")), nav, cash)\n        if marker in seen_markers:\n            continue\n        seen_markers.add(marker)\n        compact_history.append(item)\n    nav_history = compact_history\n    records: list[dict] = []\n    for idx, item in enumerate(nav_history):\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        total_value = round(nav * float(summary.get(\"paper_capital\", 0.0)), 2)\n        market_value = round(total_value - cash, 2)\n        records.append(\n            {\n                \"generated_at\": f\"{summary.get('generated_at')}#{idx+1}\",\n                \"signal_date\": item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\"),\n                \"nav\": nav,\n                \"total_value\": total_value,\n                \"cash\": cash,\n                \"market_value\": market_value,\n                \"position_count\": int(summary.get(\"position_count\", 0) or 0),","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774878633469}}
{"type":"message","id":"47bf5a17","parentId":"8ef5d839","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:50:44.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see - the breadth paper trading uses `PREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions.csv\"`. The predictions file is what's stale.The fundamental issue: the `ml_predictions.csv` is generated by training the model on historical data and running predictions. The Qlib data was refreshed but the predictions haven't been regenerated.\n\nTo fix this, I need to either:1. Run the full training script `train_ml_factors_all_a.py` to regenerate predictions\n2. Or find a way to incrementally update predictions\n\nThe `train_ml_factors_all_a.py` trains from 2019-01-01 to 2026-03-10, so it should cover the latest dates. But running this is heavy.\n\n\nI should check how long the full training takes before attempting it, and I also notice the TEST_END parameter is hardcoded to 2026-03-10 - that's likely why predictions stopped updating even though Qlib has more recent data. The script uses `train_ml_factors_all_a.py` to train a model and generate fresh predictions for the updated dates, but the TEST_END parameter is hardcoded to 2026-03-10. I need to update that to today's date (2026-03-30) and run it, though this will be computationally expensive since it retrains the model from scratch.","thinkingSignature":"a8abce9602aaf645777764f568c7172193148113e13e09dbf98228d67d736d89"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5e9iph2xi2py_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '100,130p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/train_ml_factors_all_a.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5e9iph2xi2py_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_a_all/ 2>/dev/null | head -10; ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/ 2>/dev/n